title: For Trade:  3D Printer - Makerbot Thing-O-Matic - Includes Supplies
postcontent:
Hi, and thank you for looking!

For trade-only, we have a genuine Makerbot Thing-O-Matic 3D Printer, complete with cables and supplies.

This 3D printer features a Stepstruder MK6 and 4x4x4 build platform.  It is a fully working model, and we've printed a number of whistles and other basic trinkets to test its functionality.  Additionally, we precision re-adjusted a few key mounting points, and it should be a good reliable hobbyist printer for many projects.

To answer the first question many here will undoubtedly ask, will it print AR lowers?  No.  Well, not very well, at least.  It has a 4x4x4 build area, which means that to build objects larger than 4x4x4 requires the use of various bonding methods, making it not very good for making AR lowers.  On the gun-making front, you might be able to make some nice 1911 parts, snap-caps, mags, holsters, tools, etc.  However, as far as AR lowers are concerned, it will take you HOURS to make one working lower, and since good quality aluminum lowers can be bought for cheap here on ArmsList, you're better spending your time working towards one of those.

This 3D printer will include a variety of replacement parts as well as several spools of filament.  It works well on Windows, Linux, and Mac, and if even works well without a computer.  Just put your 3D image on an SD card and tell the machine to make it!

Please remember that 3D printing is generally a hobbyist-oriented industry, and a LOT of tinkering and tweaking is usually involved.  If you have any questions, please feel free to ask.  Thanks again for looking.  (-:

CCW Training $150 / 16 hours and $75 8/hrs

Small classes, lot's of shooting, draw and live fire your pistol from your holster.

I run small classes in a private setting.  You will shoot  in this course,  200 - 300 rounds is not uncommon.  


The course will start with 4 hours of NRA FIRST Steps Pistol and it continues with 4 hours of NRA / Winchester Pistol Qualification program.  This is a self paced program and students can progress at their pace. Running small classes allows for this.

The second day starts with several hours of IL Law, Federal Law covering such topics as use of force and the IL Concealed Carry Act.  We move to drawing and firing realistic air-soft analog pistols, drawing and dry firing your pistol from your holster and finally drawing and live firing your pistol from your holster.

The course meets all requirements for your concealed carry permit.  As a courtesy veterans may take the full 16 hours for $75 if they wish.  I am a small time operation so I do not offer a 12 hour course at this time.

title: For Sale:  Air Taser+Holster Compact 15ft Range + 3 Cartridges
postcontent: Check around and see how many actual Taser units that fire probes are for sale.....Then, for those you find, how many are under $150? That is a big ZERO until now. This is the model right before the C2 that is a compact unit. It has the same 15 ft range as the C2 which is really just a curvier design. As the C2 is $350-$400 with the extras, this unit will cost less than half. Whether you want to make some seriously cool You-Tube videos or keep it next to the bed, this unit works! How do I know? Besides the photo that has the POWER light glowing, I got it with 4 cartridges and fired one. I hung a towel over a picnic pork roast (still wrapped) and at 6 or 7 feet POP!!! The probes stick in a towel like glue as they are barbed and the voltage can jump 2 inches to a body beneath, through jackets or even kevlar. Only a 9-volt battery so won't mess with a pacemaker even, but watch COPS and you will see a 280lb badazz whine how he was stabbed and shot, but the TASER beat the crap out of him. He went from "I hate the world and you too cop!" to "SIR, I give, no more...." This unit has a programmed cycle that repeats again so the "intruder" does not recover fast and yank off the probes. It cycles through a pattern so you can drop the unit and run. You can also use the unit as a TOUCH and ZAP stun gun if needed after firing (If you miss)The pack of new cartridges (not new as in for sale today at the store as this is the previous model) has all sorts of registration you send to TASER and every deployment, drops 20-50 strips of paper with the serial number of your unit all over the place. The Air Taser unit has 1 LIVE cartridge mounted (pops on and off easy) and a sealed and new pack of 2 more. As it is used and consigned, no warranty can be made by me, and all instructions and registration is direct with TASER if you choose.  At this price, you get the 2 cartridges (sell for $70) plus the 1 attached, the holster and a new Alkaline 9V battery. Not the newest model but the $175 to $200 you save can buy a decent 22 pistol (Glock Trainer) for target use or fun OR a 12 gauge pump shotgun new in box with ghost ring sights.You need an ffl for the 12 gauge but this TASER ships direct to you for $12.35

title: For Sale/Trade:  Yugo M53 MG42 Clone Semi Auto
postcontent:
This is a Wiselite Arms M53 Gen II. I got it from another reenactor and it was not used prior. He simply had it around. It could use a little "working out" to help loosen it up a bit. I have fired three live rounds out of it and about 15 blanks through it while I was attempting to get it tuned in for blanks.

This is a Yugoslavian semi-automatic only copy of the MG42. It can not be made to fire full auto.

It has a little surface dirt on the bipod from a training event. The "brown stuff" inside the cover is grease. Not dirt or rust. But it probably could use being cleaned out and regreased.

Included is a wooden box. Two belts. Yugo Snail Drum. (Could use a repaint to look more German wartime) and I will throw in my MG Gunner's pouch as I will not need it. I also have a MG42 sling that I will include but I do not recommend using it as the latch for the pistol grip is not big enough. However, I have no use for it and maybe you could modify it or something.

This is NOT CONVERTED. It is still chambered in 8mm Mauser. Some people convert them to 308. This is still in it's default caliber.

I also am including an MG3 blank adapter but I do not recommend this for use. There are other blank adapters out there that are far superior and will give you good results. This gun will likely need some tuning in for blanks. They can be a bit stubborn with blanks but a proper adapter and time will go a LONG way. This is just how these guns are.

I am asking 3000 plus half on shipping costs. I will be kind on that rather than tossing the full cost of shipping at you. I will be at Knox County D-Day in Ohio if you wish to do a FTF there. Any FTF sale will require ID. I heavily prefer if you have a valid Ohio CHL to show me to show you are valid to own firearms.

I reserve the right to refuse a sale. If you raise red-flags I will back down in the effort to keep this legal.

For trades? I'm not too sure yet. I am seeking German or Russian weapons. BFONGs or otherwise. I might dabble in some modern stuff. We'll play that by ear. Money, obviously, is king.

Payment via PayPal usually preferred. We will keep it discreet to avoid them getting antsy about it. I may take other Payment methods. However, NO CASHIER CHECKS! This is due to the risks involved with them. Thanks for understanding. FTF, obviously, cash is king there.

SERIOUS INQUIRIES ONLY PLEASE. Been having issues on other pages with this item and lack of commitment! Come prepared and things will go smooth.
